# CourtOps Code Ownership
#
# When a PR touches files matching these patterns, the listed owner(s)
# are automatically requested for review. This is informational — it
# doesn't block merging, it just flags "hey, this touches something core."
#
# HOW TO USE: If you build something a specific way for a specific reason,
# add yourself here with a comment explaining why. Example:
#
#   # Auth rework — uses specific session handling for multi-tenant isolation
#   src/lib/auth/                        @your-github-username
#
# Since .github/ is owned below, your CODEOWNERS change will flag Sami
# for review — so both of you know what's protected and why.

